{
  "stem": "15694.12",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But our legs-- anyway, and the worst of that was that one of them had diarrhea.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The next day, I asked them, if they give me the blanket-- the only they had-- I will get out of the bed.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And next to the bed was a table.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And kneeling on the table was-- because it wasn't big enough-- and with my hands on my-- my head on my folded arms, that's how I slept the next night.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I'm not sure if another night after that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But shortly, the man with the diarrhea-- a man came and put the name, and I'm not sure how he knew his name-- L-E-V-I on his chest.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Now, why he did that, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But this man was taken away soon, the one with the diarrhea.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I was glad to go back into the bed with four-- I mean, now we were only four.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] well, now the Russians were, of course-- first they were like Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And then they got smaller.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Then there was a loaf of bread for four.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And then it was for six, then for eight, and even for 10, and maybe nothing.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But ice developed, you know, again.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Let me explain it a different way.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I liked conjuring tricks as a child.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And it came, sort of, to my help at this particular moment and sometimes also during the war, war years.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "A, a big can of soup for, for the barracks were put in the middle of the barracks.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "The beds were, like, three high-- three beds high, containing between 12 and 15 people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And next to it, directly next to each other, another one containing-- and then there was a little gap, and so on.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
